== Clarification for AOL users ==
AOL users are constantly being caught by blocks, either as a result of autoblocks of registered vandals, or by those who take advantage their round-robin method of doling out IP addresses.  As much as I would prefer to see this page kept as simple as possible, I think it would behoove us to add a link explaining why they are being innocently blocked in greater detail, similar to how we have a '''"Editing from China?"''' link at the bottom of the page.  Best regards, [[User:Hall Monitor|Hall Monitor]] 18:37, 24 March 2006 (UTC)

:Doesn't the "Innocent?" section cover this topic, albeit briefly, already? Maybe a link to such a page could be inserted in that section; it seems like a good idea, though. Thanks! [[User:Flcelloguy|Flcelloguy]] <small>([[User talk:Flcelloguy|A <font color="brown">note?</font>]])</small> 21:42, 24 March 2006 (UTC)

:I support this idea.  The real question is, what should the page say?  The German Wikipedia [[:de:AOL-Sperre|seems to suggest]] that simply using a different browser (such as [[Firefox]]) will bypass the AOL proxies.  Can anyone confirm this?  Can the AOL standard browsers ([[Internet Explorer|IE]] on Windows, [[Mozilla]]-based on Mac) be configured not to use the proxies?  Where couls we find a few AOL users to help us test this in practice?  —[[User:Ilmari Karonen|Ilmari Karonen]] <small>([[User talk:Ilmari Karonen|talk]])</small> 16:49, 26 March 2006 (UTC)

