===Fixed!===
As of today, the page shown to blocked users [[bugzilla:4990|now includes the source]] of the page they were trying to edit.  Even more importantly, if the user is blocked ''while'' they are editing, the message they see will show the version they were about to submit.  Thus, '''IE users will no longer lose their edits''' if their IP is blocked while editing.  I'm sure millions of AOLers will appreciate this.  (Ps. Two new messages have been introduced for this feature: [[MediaWiki:blockedoriginalsource|blockedoriginalsource]] and [[MediaWiki:blockededitsource|blockededitsource]].  Their purpose should be obvious.)  —[[User:Ilmari Karonen|Ilmari Karonen]] <small>([[User talk:Ilmari Karonen|talk]])</small> 22:49, 24 June 2006 (UTC)
:This is one of the most positive developments in Wikipedia so far. --<font style="background:gold">[[WP:EA|<font color="green">S</font>]][[User:Siva1979|iva1979]]</font><sup><font style="background:yellow">[[User talk:Siva1979|Talk to me]]</font></sup> 20:34, 15 July 2006 (UTC)

